        { "mark": "M1", "desc": "Denominator factorised: $(x - 3)(x + 2)$" },
        { "mark": "A1", "desc": "$\\dfrac{3(x-2)}{x-3}$ cao" }
      ],
      "workingSteps": [
        "Numerator: $3x^2 - 12 = 3(x^2 - 4) = 3(x-2)(x+2)$",
        "Denominator: $x^2 - x - 6$; need product $-6$, sum $-1$: $-3$ and $+2$",
        "$x^2 - x - 6 = (x-3)(x+2)$",
        "$\\dfrac{3(x-2)(x+2)}{(x-3)(x+2)} = \\dfrac{3(x-2)}{x-3}$",
        "Check $x=4$: $\\frac{3(16)-12}{16-4-6}=\\frac{36}{6}=6$; answer: $\\frac{3(2)}{1}=6$ ✓"
      ],
      "explanation": "Factorise numerator and denominator fully, then cancel the common factor."
